Learning Outcomes
  What is responsive design?
    designing your website to be accessible to a different variety of screen sizes

  Why is responsive design important to your users?
    accessibility

  How do you make a "fluid" layout?
    using media queries and responsive design patterns like grid, flexbox, or CSS frameworks

  What are Media Queries?
    queries you can put into your CSS that are only called upon for certain screen sizes
    it allows you to have a different set of CSS rules applied to different screen sizes

  How do you use media queries to make your website responsive?
    by designing your website for different screen sizes accordingly for different media queries


Media Query
  Example:
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" media="screen and (max-device-width: 480px)" href="sheet.css">

  This has a media type and the actual query enclosed within parentheses

  Example
    @media screen and (max-width: 600px) {
      ...
    }


Viewport
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    sets the width of the viewport to the width of the device and sets the initial zoom level to 1.0
    page content will be displayed 1:1

50-75 characters is the established maximum comfort of line length

max-width is important


Response Web Design
  Flexible Grid
  Flexible Images
    img { width: 100%; height: auto; }
  CSS3 Media Queries and Screen Resolutions

Breakpoints: When your site reaches a certain viewing width, and callsnew style for that width (i.e. media query)


Respond.js and Modernizr.js are javascript solutions that bring the power of CSS3/HTML5 to non-supporting browsers
